about.summary: It provides 30 indexes for determining the optimal number of clusters in a data set and offers the best clustering scheme from different results to the user.

name: r-nbclust
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '3.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-nbclust
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/NbClust_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/NbClust/NbClust_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 6cf041a7a22661b59eb9eddbee71c5c80214438ccfba8a6f6bc152e33f228bef

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1002
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('NbClust')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('NbClust')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://sites.google.com/site/malikacharrad/research/nbclust-package
  license: GPL-2
  summary: 'It provides 30 indexes for determining the optimal number of clusters in a data set
    and offers the best clustering scheme from different results to the user. '
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
